The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 21: The empowered group of ministers (EGoM) will meet here tomorrow to decide on raising the present cap of allowing only 150 special economic zones in the country in the face of 200 pending proposals apart from 140 already cleared. The EGoM, headed by defence minister Pranab Mukherjee, is meeting at a time when there are sharp differences between the commerce and finance ministries over SEZs.

 New Delhi, Aug. 21: Telecom regulator Trai has decided to maintain a status quo position on the interconnection usage charges (IUC) for short message service on mobile phones in a major relief to operators and subscribers.

 Mumbai, Aug. 21: Kochi Refineries Ltd (KRL) has received an approval from the ministry of company affairs to merge with Bharat Petroleum Corporation Ltd. 

 Mumbai, Aug. 21: To increase its presence in South Africa, Tata Steel Kzn has commenced construction of its ferrochrome plant in that country. 

 Panaji, Aug. 21: Bangalore-based Desk to Desk Courier (DTDC) will move to China from this September. The company has signed a service agreement with Hong Kong-headquartered Kerry logistic company which will be DTDCs service provider in China.




